1 AMEND House Committee Substitute for House Bill Nos. 3068 & 3049, Page 7, Section 43.530,
2 Line 23, by inserting after said section and line the following:
3
4 "320.405. 1. For purposes of this section, the following terms mean:
5 (1) "Division", the Missouri division of fire safety within the department of public
6 safety;
7 (2) "Missouri fire and life safety standards", minimum fire-protection and life-safety
8 requirements adopted by the division under this section, informed by nationally recognized fire
9 and building safety principles including, but not limited to, best practices reflected in the
10 International Fire Code (IFC), the International Building Code (IBC), and applicable National
11 Fire Protection Association (NFPA) standards, without adopting any model code in whole;
12 (3) "State-inspected facility", any building or occupancy required under Missouri law or
13 regulation to undergo fire-safety inspections conducted by, or under the authority of, the
14 division.
15 2. (1) No later than July 1, 2027, the division shall, by rule, adopt Missouri fire and life
16 safety standards establishing minimum requirements for fire protection, means of egress, fire
17 resistance, detection and alarm systems, suppression systems, emergency operations, and related
18 safety measures for state-inspected facilities.
19 (2) The division may incorporate by reference specific technical provisions, methods,
20 formulas, or performance criteria derived from nationally recognized fire and building safety
21 standards, provided that no model code shall be adopted in whole.
22 (3) The division may adopt amendments, exceptions, or Missouri-specific modifications
23 as necessary to account for regional conditions, facility types, or statutory requirements.
24 (4) The division shall review the Missouri fire and life safety standards at least every
25 five years and may update such standards by rule under chapter 536.
26 3. Beginning January 1, 2028, the Missouri fire and life safety standards shall apply to a
27 state-inspected facility under any of the following conditions:
28 (1) Initial construction of a state-inspected facility;
29 (2) Major renovation affecting means of egress, detection, alarm, or suppression
30 systems;
Action Taken___________________________________________ Date __________________
