6771H02.05H
1 (3) Transfer of ownership, including sale, conveyance, merger, or change in controlling
2 interest; and
3 (4) Any addition, alteration, or series of related improvements to a state-inspected
4 facility that, in aggregate, are reasonably determined by the division to constitute a substantial
5 improvement, meaning construction, reconstruction, rehabilitation, or installation work where
6 the total cost or scope of work equals or exceeds fifty percent of the facility's pre-improvement
7 market value. For purposes of this subdivision, a formal appraisal shall not be required, and the
8 division may rely on reasonable cost estimates, permit valuations, construction contracts, or the
9 nature of the work performed including, but not limited to, the installation of new fire protection,
10 detection, alarm, or suppression systems.
11 4. Except as provided in subsection 3 of this section, state-inspected facilities existing
12 prior to August 28, 2026, shall be considered lawfully nonconforming and shall not be required
13 to comply with the Missouri fire and life safety standards.
14 5. (1) Nothing in this section shall prohibit any city, county, or fire protection district
15 from adopting requirements more stringent than the Missouri fire and life safety standards.
16 (2) No political subdivision shall apply standards less stringent than the Missouri fire
17 and life safety standards to any facility regulated under this section.
18 (3) Nothing in this section shall be construed as creating a statewide building or fire code
19 applicable to any occupancy not already subject to inspection by the division.
20 6. (1) Compliance with the Missouri fire and life safety standards shall be verified
21 through inspections conducted by the division or an authorized local jurisdiction.
22 (2) A state-inspected facility shall not be licensed, certified, or approved for operation
23 unless the division determines that the facility meets the applicable requirements of this section.
24 (3) The division may issue correction orders, reinspections, or occupancy limitations as
25 authorized by law.
26 7. Any rule or portion of a rule, as that term is defined in section 536.010, that is created
27 under the authority delegated in this section shall become effective only if it complies with and is
28 subject to all of the provisions of chapter 536 and, if applicable, section 536.028. This section
29 and chapter 536 are nonseverable and if any of the powers vested with the general assembly
30 pursuant to chapter 536 to review, to delay the effective date, or to disapprove and annul a rule
31 are subsequently held unconstitutional, then the grant of rulemaking authority and any rule
32 proposed or adopted after August 28, 2026, shall be invalid and void."; and
33
34 Further amend said bill, Page 39, Section 589.417, Line 27, by inserting after said section and
35 line the following:
36
